dcterms:description: The MAREA gait database contains time series collected from accelerometers placed on the ankles of participants and Force Sensitive Resistors (FSR) placed on their heels and toes while walking under different conditions. It includes sequences of accelerometer data and independently detected and synchronized events.
dcterms:title: MAREA gait database

dcterms:description: The UCR Time Series Classification Archive is a collection of time series datasets used for classification tasks. It provides a variety of datasets that can be utilized for benchmarking time series classification algorithms.
dcterms:title: UCR Time Series Classification Archive
